I simply won't do it. I purge things regularly. I live in a small space. But even so, I keep finding things. It's a seemingly endless process. 

I cannot wait to be finished and to be able to use everything and know where it all is!
I always held onto things because they were special to Mom or belonged to a family member but these were at Mom's urgings and she hoards.
I've never gifted myself these things, never taken the time to truly examine where my precious items should live and even if they are precious to ME.
Marie Kondo finds homes for each item that sparks joy. It's so delightful when everything has a place. It takes thought and care and slowing down and planning.
My neurodivergent cleaning group spends a lot of time talking about doom boxes. (Don't organize, only move.) Boxes full of odds and ends with no home. It's a common habit.
I only have one real doom corner left in the apartment. There are laundry baskets and extra pillows and all my musical instruments in it, plus scrapbooks. Soon, everything will have a home.
My daughter has already done half the chores on her chart. I think she is pushing for her allowance. 😂 We are both so excited for the new schedule change.
Creating takes courage and to make something and have someone GET it is amazing. They don't need to hear from every person that doesn't get it.
